
  Summary

  1. Created AssignmentsCoreService (/core/services/assignments_core_service.py)

  A new content management service for Assignment entities with:
  - CRUD operations: get_assignment, update_assignment, delete_assignment
  - Time-based queries: get_assignment_for_date, get_recent_assignments
  - Status workflow: publish_assignment, archive_assignment, mark_as_draft
  - Category management: categorize_assignment, get_assignments_by_category
  - Tag management: add_tags, remove_tags, get_assignments_by_tag
  - Bulk operations: bulk_categorize, bulk_tag, bulk_delete
  - Export: export_to_markdown
  - Journal-specific convenience methods: get_journal_for_date, get_journals_by_category, publish_journal, archive_journal

  2. Updated services_bootstrap.py

  - Added import for AssignmentsCoreService
  - Created assignments_core_service instance with the assignments backend
  - Added assignments_core field to the Services dataclass
  - Included assignments_core_service in the Services container initialization

  3. Updated  assignments_content_api.py

  Routes now use AssignmentsCoreService for content management operations:
  - /api/journals/date/{target_date} - Uses assignments_core.get_journal_for_date()
  - /api/journals/{uid}/publish - Uses assignments_core.publish_journal()
  - /api/journals/{uid}/archive - Uses assignments_core.archive_journal()
  - /api/journals/category/{category} - Uses assignments_core.get_journals_by_category()
  - /api/journals/{uid}/tags - Uses assignments_core.add_tags()
  - /api/journals/tag/{tag} - Uses assignments_core.get_assignments_by_tag() (filtered to JOURNAL type)
  - /api/journals/bulk/categorize - Uses assignments_core.bulk_categorize()
  - /api/journals/bulk/tag - Uses assignments_core.bulk_tag()
  - /api/journals/{uid}/export/markdown - Uses assignments_core.export_to_markdown()


  Two API Files - Clear Separation:

  | File                       | Purpose                                                 | Dependencies                                           |
  |----------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------|
  | assignments_api.py         | File lifecycle (upload, download, process)              | AssignmentSubmissionService, ProcessingPipelineService |
  | assignments_content_api.py | Content management (categories, tags, search, bulk ops) | AssignmentsCoreService, JournalsService                |

  Route Prefixes:
  - Both now use /api/assignments/ prefix
  - File ops: /api/assignments/upload, /api/assignments/{uid}/download
  - Content ops: /api/assignments/search, /api/assignments/by-category/{category}


  Architecture Clarification

  - JournalsService: AI transcript processing (process_raw_transcript, search_journals) - unchanged
  - AssignmentsCoreService: Content management (categories, tags, publish/archive, bulk ops) - NEW
  - AssignmentSubmissionService: File upload and storage - unchanged
  - JournalCoreService: DEPRECATED - use AssignmentsCoreService instead

